31:48.204 --> 31:51.141
Mm. Maybe you've written yours.

31:52.542 --> 31:53.510
Ah.

31:54.444 --> 31:57.379
Serena,
I read a glowing review

31:57.381 --> 31:59.280
<i>of your jewelry online.</i>

31:59.282 --> 32:03.051
Either I wrote that
or I fucked the person who did.

32:03.053 --> 32:05.253
<i>Oh, I think you're being
too hard on yourself.</i>

32:05.255 --> 32:07.221
I think
you're an amazing designer.

32:07.223 --> 32:10.160
Thank you. And I think you're
gonna have an amazing hotel.

32:11.528 --> 32:12.797
I do, too.

32:49.665 --> 32:51.499
Oh.

32:51.501 --> 32:53.701
What are you even doing here?

32:53.703 --> 32:56.371
Hazel's doing fine,
she doesn't need this.

32:56.373 --> 32:57.572
What about me?

32:57.574 --> 32:59.040
Maybe I need this.

32:59.042 --> 33:00.441
Shall I tell you
where the last six...

33:00.443 --> 33:01.709
- Don't you...
- Shall I tell her?

33:01.711 --> 33:03.545
Don't you dare
say a word to her.

33:03.547 --> 33:04.912
Or what?

33:04.914 --> 33:06.480
You'll what?

33:06.482 --> 33:08.449
Keep your voice down, okay?

33:08.451 --> 33:09.817
What is it you want?

33:09.819 --> 33:11.686
- Do you want money?
- I don't need your money.

33:11.688 --> 33:14.488
- I can look after myself.
- Can you?

33:14.490 --> 33:15.759
<i>Can you, hm?</i>

33:18.595 --> 33:21.162
It happened,
but now it's time to...

33:21.164 --> 33:22.432
Move on?

33:24.634 --> 33:26.738
Is that what you hate me for?

33:28.038 --> 33:30.505
You think I don't spend
every waking moment

33:30.507 --> 33:32.908
thinking about that day?

33:32.910 --> 33:35.309
You think I don't feel it
the way you do?

33:35.311 --> 33:37.912
You really think
I don't feel it?

33:37.914 --> 33:39.182
Feel what?

33:40.584 --> 33:43.250
What don't you feel?

33:43.252 --> 33:45.856
Serena thinks
I don't emote enough.

33:52.563 --> 33:54.028
I'm gonna have a glass of wine.

34:18.054 --> 34:20.054
"Seas the day."

34:20.056 --> 34:21.922
- What'd you say?
- That couldn't be right.

34:21.925 --> 34:23.257
<i>"S-E-A-S."</i>

34:23.260 --> 34:26.197
<i>Shouldn't that be spelled
S-E-I-Z-E?</i>

34:27.530 --> 34:29.764
I'm good, thanks.

34:29.766 --> 34:30.898
<i>Well, excuse me.</i>

34:30.900 --> 34:32.166
You drop that,
you're paying for it.

34:40.476 --> 34:41.445
Hey.

34:43.280 --> 34:45.679
Don't I know you?

34:45.681 --> 34:47.617
I don't think so.

34:49.152 --> 34:51.820
Maybe. I... I did have a book.

34:53.824 --> 34:55.760
Pretty sure
we don't know each other.

34:57.793 --> 34:59.126
Enjoy your coffee.

35:16.813 --> 35:18.749
<i>Sorry, sir. He pushed me.</i>

35:22.686 --> 35:24.288
Alright, let's go.

35:30.860 --> 35:32.927
You could be expelled
for that.

35:39.735 --> 35:41.672
Get out of here.

35:48.644 --> 35:51.845
Lady Macbeth,
what do we know about her?

35:51.847 --> 35:53.347
What's she like?

35:53.349 --> 35:55.217
<i>She's a tough bitch.</i>

35:55.219 --> 35:58.519
She is a tough bitch.
But listen to this.

35:58.521 --> 36:02.523
"Come to my woman's breasts
and take my milk for gall."

36:02.525 --> 36:04.059
Woman's breasts. Ha-ha-ha.

36:04.061 --> 36:06.260
Gall, what is it?

36:06.262 --> 36:08.729
They made Christ drink it
on the cross.

36:08.731 --> 36:11.465
- Vinegar.
- Right.

36:11.467 --> 36:14.034
So, she wants the milk in her
breasts to turn to vinegar

36:14.036 --> 36:17.104
which raises the question,
why is she lactating?

36:18.608 --> 36:19.974
Producing milk, dickheads.

36:19.976 --> 36:22.110
And? Tell 'em why.

36:22.112 --> 36:23.711
She's pregnant.

36:23.713 --> 36:26.380
"I have given suck
and know how tender

36:26.382 --> 36:29.650
'tis to love the babe
that milks me."

36:29.652 --> 36:32.153
But there's no baby Macbeth
in this play.

36:32.155 --> 36:34.488
- So?
- It died.

36:34.490 --> 36:36.657
And since she's still lactating?

36:36.659 --> 36:38.492
Just died.

36:38.494 --> 36:43.398
A tough bitch,
a woman's baby has just died.

36:43.400 --> 36:45.670
Enough to drive her crazy
with grief.

36:46.737 --> 36:48.970
And Macbeth..

36:48.972 --> 36:50.304
...we were told
in the very beginning

36:50.306 --> 36:52.307
that he was fearless in battle

36:52.309 --> 36:54.541
that he would just throw himself
at the enemy.

36:54.543 --> 36:56.646
<i>Didn't care whether he lived
or died.</i>

36:58.347 --> 37:00.282
He was heartbroken.

37:00.284 --> 37:03.418
And he'll move heaven and earth
to make it right again.

38:13.623 --> 38:15.289
- <i>Daddy.</i>
- <i>Come on, Daddy.</i>

38:15.291 --> 38:17.025
Don't just lie there
like a big lump.

38:17.027 --> 38:19.293
Help Mommy build..
What's it called again?

38:19.295 --> 38:21.195
- A moat.
- A moat.

38:21.197 --> 38:23.865
- A boat?
- <i>A moat, dipstick.</i>

38:23.867 --> 38:25.333
- Ah!
- Daddy's a dipstick.

38:25.335 --> 38:29.106
Oh, is that so? Well, you just
watch this dipstick dig.

38:30.773 --> 38:34.045
Molly, you get the bucket
and go get some water, honey.

38:35.878 --> 38:37.845
I'm sorry, did we wake you?

38:37.847 --> 38:38.815
What?

38:44.855 --> 38:47.255
- Flags, Mommy.
- <i>Oh.</i>

39:49.952 --> 39:51.920
The sandcastle.

39:51.922 --> 39:54.021
You remember the day
we built a big sandcastle?

39:54.023 --> 39:55.824
- <i>You, me and Molly?</i>
- What?

39:55.826 --> 39:57.758
What time is it?

39:57.760 --> 39:59.293
Ugh! Where were you?

39:59.295 --> 40:01.095
- I tried calling you.
- The sandcastle.

40:01.097 --> 40:03.298
The one, the big one
with the moat, right?

40:03.300 --> 40:04.766
And we had the little red flags?

40:04.768 --> 40:05.900
What are you talking about?

40:05.902 --> 40:07.001
Tell me you remember.

40:07.003 --> 40:09.940
Yeah, the red flags, I remember.

40:15.778 --> 40:17.244
You wanna build a sandcastle?

40:17.246 --> 40:19.546
"Seas the day."

40:19.548 --> 40:20.648
I've been seeing it everywhere.

40:20.650 --> 40:21.916
It was written in the sand.

40:21.918 --> 40:24.686
- On my computer.
- What are you talking about?

40:24.688 --> 40:25.787
Oh, fuck, you're drunk.

40:25.789 --> 40:28.025
Maybe, but it doesn't matter..

40:29.492 --> 40:31.429
...'cause I think
I figured it out.

40:32.728 --> 40:35.597
I have had the exact same dream
now, twice

40:35.599 --> 40:38.266
about the day
we built the sandcastle..

40:38.268 --> 40:40.534
...except I don't think
it's a dream.

40:40.536 --> 40:42.836
It's like it's a, a message

40:42.838 --> 40:46.039
a message from someone
or something.

40:46.041 --> 40:48.709
- You're scaring me.
- Just listen to me, please.

40:48.711 --> 40:50.278
Okay?

40:50.280 --> 40:52.246
When I first woke up,
"Seas the day"

40:52.248 --> 40:54.481
was written in the sand.

40:54.483 --> 40:57.284
Tonight you handed me the flag

40:57.286 --> 40:58.720
to stick into the sandcastle

40:58.722 --> 41:01.158
only the dream ended
before I could do it.

41:02.492 --> 41:04.428
When I woke up..

41:05.295 --> 41:07.595
...I still had the flag.

41:07.597 --> 41:09.533
It was in my hand, Hazel.

41:11.001 --> 41:12.766
I don't understand.

41:12.768 --> 41:14.269
"Seas the day."

41:14.271 --> 41:15.873
It's a..

41:16.907 --> 41:19.173
It's like
a childish misspelling.

41:19.175 --> 41:22.409
It's supposed
to be like S-E-I-Z-E.

41:22.411 --> 41:25.146
It means seize <i>that</i> day.

41:25.148 --> 41:28.081
What if it means seize <i>her?</i>

41:28.083 --> 41:30.517
- Who?
- Molly.

41:30.519 --> 41:32.452
And instead of holding
the red flag

41:32.454 --> 41:34.222
when the dream ended

41:34.224 --> 41:36.423
what I if I was holding
onto her hand?

41:36.425 --> 41:37.825
What if I could pull her
out of that dream?

41:37.827 --> 41:39.927
- Ben...
- You know, pull her out of that day.

41:39.929 --> 41:41.496
- Don't you hear yourself?
- No, because we could change it.

41:41.498 --> 41:44.434
- We could change the past.
- Don't you hear yourself?

41:46.769 --> 41:48.706
I know what I saw.

41:53.242 --> 41:54.844
<i>Ben, please.</i>

42:02.418 --> 42:04.687
I've thought a lot
about that day, too.

42:06.523 --> 42:08.856
That was the day
the boat came round the point

42:08.858 --> 42:10.794
and you were out swimming.

42:13.429 --> 42:14.795
I've often wondered
what would have...

42:14.797 --> 42:15.765
What?

42:19.802 --> 42:21.536
If it had hit me?

42:21.538 --> 42:24.307
Maybe Molly wouldn't have
fallen down the stairs?

42:25.775 --> 42:28.711
You were supposed
to be looking after her.

42:30.981 --> 42:34.084
You were
supposed to be minding her.

42:59.509 --> 43:02.809
<i>Lack of sleep is usually
consistent with stress.</i>

43:02.811 --> 43:06.179
Your recent bereavement
is undoubtedly a factor

43:06.181 --> 43:08.749
but rather than prescribing
sleeping pills, perhaps...

43:08.751 --> 43:10.688
I'm also a teacher.

43:12.822 --> 43:14.992
One a night.

43:15.724 --> 43:16.923
You hear me?

43:16.925 --> 43:18.862
<i>Strictly one a night.</i>

44:20.789 --> 44:23.324
- <i>Come on, Daddy.</i>
- <i>Yeah, come on, Daddy.</i>

44:23.326 --> 44:25.126
<i>Don't just lie there
like a big lump.</i>

44:25.128 --> 44:27.327
<i>Help Mommy build..
What's it called again?</i>

44:27.329 --> 44:29.599
- A moat.
- <i>A moat.</i>

44:31.201 --> 44:34.271
Look, Molly, Daddy's diggin'.

44:36.206 --> 44:37.371
Daddy's a dipstick, huh?

44:37.373 --> 44:40.277
Molly, get the bucket,
go get some water.

44:41.077 --> 44:43.013
<i>Run. Run, run, run.</i>

44:45.581 --> 44:47.882
<i>I'm sorry, did we wake you?</i>

44:47.884 --> 44:49.717
- <i>What?</i>
- <i>Huh.</i>

44:49.719 --> 44:51.619
Cut the tortured writer crap.

44:51.621 --> 44:53.557
You're complex, I get it.

44:58.695 --> 45:00.297
<i>Flags, Mommy.</i>

45:10.873 --> 45:12.809
How did you get that?

45:15.911 --> 45:17.043
Ah.

45:17.045 --> 45:19.045
- Big hug, huh?
- Big hug.

45:21.016 --> 45:22.285
Don't let go.

46:04.059 --> 46:07.061
If I had died..

46:07.063 --> 46:09.333
...wouldn't you try
to contact me?

46:12.101 --> 46:14.104
'Cause I'd find a way.

46:16.338 --> 46:17.607
I would.

46:25.614 --> 46:28.050
I'm sorry I said
those things to you.

47:09.324 --> 47:11.060
<i>A moat.</i>

47:46.195 --> 47:47.695
<i>Time travel?</i>

47:47.697 --> 47:50.697
Jesus, Ben, I teach physics,
not science fiction.

47:50.699 --> 47:52.666
To a particular point.

47:52.668 --> 47:54.101
One particular day.

47:54.103 --> 47:55.903
I mean Hawking
said it's possible

47:55.905 --> 47:57.003
he said that, didn't he?

47:57.005 --> 47:58.338
Yeah, he also said that

47:58.340 --> 48:00.374
if time travel
were to ever exist

48:00.376 --> 48:02.976
then we probably would have
already met time travelers.

48:02.978 --> 48:05.211
- Maybe we have.
- <i>An infinite universe?</i>

48:05.213 --> 48:07.882
<i>I guess anything's possible.</i>

48:07.884 --> 48:09.684
Whatever you're working on,
it sounds mad

48:09.686 --> 48:11.622
I can't wait to read it.

48:13.222 --> 48:14.291
You okay?

48:15.925 --> 48:16.927
I'm fine.

48:28.603 --> 48:31.207
Everybody,
just open your books.

48:39.916 --> 48:42.349
- You can't just burst in here.
- This is important.

48:42.351 --> 48:44.184
How do I pull the cameras up?

48:44.186 --> 48:46.420
A phone's been stolen.
Denise, right?

48:46.422 --> 48:48.555
- Bernice.
- Bernice, can you help me?

48:48.557 --> 48:50.494
Don't know about this.

48:52.362 --> 48:54.362
Great, can I? Thanks.

49:02.371 --> 49:05.039
- Come on.
- What do you think you're doing?

49:05.041 --> 49:08.342
Mr. Slater says a phone's been
stolen from his classroom.

49:08.344 --> 49:10.947
You have no right
to access that computer.

49:12.849 --> 49:15.215
<i>Mr. Slater, I am asking you
for the last time...</i>

49:15.217 --> 49:17.952
Give me a Goddamn second,
will you?

49:27.563 --> 49:28.532
Jesus.

49:30.065 --> 49:31.033
Stop.

50:41.570 --> 50:42.838
<i>Molly, wait!</i>

50:49.811 --> 50:51.080
<i>Molly!</i>

51:21.043 --> 51:22.012
Ben.

51:27.717 --> 51:30.550
It's the one bit of Latin
that everybody knows.

51:30.552 --> 51:33.621
<i>Carpe diem,</i> seize the day.

51:33.623 --> 51:37.258
Yeah, except it's "Seas."
S-E-A-S.

51:37.260 --> 51:39.059
I've been seeing
it everywhere.

51:39.061 --> 51:40.997
It's like the words
are haunting me.

51:43.365 --> 51:45.900
Look, if you're hoping
I'd perform an exorcism..

51:45.902 --> 51:48.101
Well, I'm sorry, my friend

51:48.103 --> 51:49.603
<i>but the pope relieved me
of those duties</i>

51:49.605 --> 51:50.873
<i>many years ago.</i>

51:57.646 --> 51:59.748
<i>Jesus, you're doin' all right,
aren't you?</i>

52:03.719 --> 52:05.655
Right, here we are.

52:13.963 --> 52:16.133
Oi, Ben, come here to me.

52:23.271 --> 52:26.740
Go and see a shrink,
you fucking lunatic.

52:41.224 --> 52:42.192
Hazel?

52:53.702 --> 52:54.670
Hazel?

53:19.494 --> 53:22.862
Oh, Benjamin Bunny.

53:22.864 --> 53:24.565
- Hi, baby.
- Hm.

53:24.567 --> 53:27.101
<i>Lose the shoes,
join the party.</i>

53:27.103 --> 53:30.271
I found it
in your jacket pocket.

53:30.273 --> 53:31.405
Weren't you gonna share?

53:31.407 --> 53:33.974
I confiscated that
from a kid at school.

53:33.976 --> 53:37.478
- Ooh.
- Hm, confiscate some more.

53:37.480 --> 53:40.750
- <i>It's good shit.</i>
- <i>It's so good.</i>

53:45.288 --> 53:47.224
Alright, give me some of that.

53:50.726 --> 53:51.695
Hm.

54:02.505 --> 54:04.438
Jesus.

54:04.440 --> 54:06.539
How long's it been?

54:06.541 --> 54:08.978
- A long time.
- Hm.

54:10.679 --> 54:14.414
In college we used to smoke
every single night.

54:14.416 --> 54:16.316
Not every single night.

54:16.318 --> 54:19.353
I mean, m... maybe you did
but I... I was innocent.

54:19.355 --> 54:21.155
You were never that innocent.

54:21.157 --> 54:22.690
<i>People always thought
I was the wild one.</i>

54:22.692 --> 54:24.191
<i>Because you are.</i>

54:24.193 --> 54:26.129
Give me that.

54:34.737 --> 54:36.537
<i>Serena has a secret.</i>

54:36.539 --> 54:39.039
<i>No. No, Hazel.</i>

54:39.041 --> 54:42.312
Serena is not
who you think she is.

54:52.755 --> 54:57.193
Serena is not her real name.

54:59.494 --> 55:01.764
Oh. Really?

55:03.199 --> 55:05.135
What's your real name?

55:05.634 --> 55:06.603
Rose.

55:09.871 --> 55:11.637
Rose, okay.

55:11.639 --> 55:14.340
Yeah, I named her Serena
on the first day of college.

55:14.342 --> 55:16.510
- Mm-hm.
- Uh-huh.

55:16.512 --> 55:18.782
A rose by any other name..

55:22.083 --> 55:25.187
...is still a rose.

55:38.067 --> 55:41.170
Ah, I love chocolate.

55:46.708 --> 55:49.642
Who knew chocolate
could taste so good?

55:49.644 --> 55:51.748
We have to put this
on the menu.

55:53.715 --> 55:56.318
I always think of my mother
when I bake.

56:04.994 --> 56:06.596
Hey, what's wrong?

56:08.764 --> 56:10.032
What is it?

56:11.833 --> 56:12.999
The dancer.

56:15.137 --> 56:17.804
What's going on?
Hey, it's okay.

56:20.443 --> 56:22.379
<i>Oh, it's okay, it's okay.</i>

56:23.878 --> 56:25.981
<i>Shh.</i>

56:28.150 --> 56:30.086
There's something
she's not telling me.

56:31.519 --> 56:33.787
Something terrible.

56:33.789 --> 56:35.688
I asked her
why she cut herself

56:35.690 --> 56:37.391
and you know what she said?

56:37.393 --> 56:38.958
Hm.

56:38.960 --> 56:41.494
That she was doing penance.

56:41.496 --> 56:44.430
- For what?
- Uh..

56:44.432 --> 56:46.432
You need to be nicer to her.

56:46.434 --> 56:49.202
- I'm always nice to her.
- No, you're not.

56:49.204 --> 56:51.304
I know she can be hard work
sometimes.

56:51.306 --> 56:52.908
You think?

56:54.577 --> 56:57.778
You know, in her eyes,
I had it all.

56:57.780 --> 57:01.581
A beautiful house,
beautiful child.

57:01.583 --> 57:02.851
Perfect husband.

57:03.885 --> 57:05.822
And I did for a while.

57:07.789 --> 57:09.726
She's here because
she's lost..

57:12.427 --> 57:14.894
...and I'm glad she's here.

57:14.896 --> 57:16.762
No, really, I am, it's..

57:16.764 --> 57:18.233
It's given me perspective.

57:20.101 --> 57:23.804
You know, there were days when
I didn't think I could go on.

57:23.806 --> 57:26.242
It would have been
so much easier to just..

57:27.576 --> 57:29.543
You remember how many pills
they prescribed me?

57:29.545 --> 57:31.481
Don't talk like that.

57:32.514 --> 57:34.451
But I don't feel
that way anymore.

57:36.918 --> 57:39.021
I feel like I can live again.

57:46.394 --> 57:48.331
There's something
I wanna show you.

57:48.898 --> 57:49.865
What?

57:51.500 --> 57:52.501
Come on.

57:53.501 --> 57:55.438
No, you tell me first.

57:57.438 --> 57:59.338
You trust me?

57:59.340 --> 58:01.374
You're wasted.

58:01.376 --> 58:02.476
Answer.

58:02.478 --> 58:04.414
You trust me, right?

58:06.715 --> 58:07.684
Yes.

58:10.119 --> 58:12.151
Come, you won't regret it.

58:12.153 --> 58:13.422
You're crazy.

58:21.697 --> 58:22.699
Come on.

58:27.101 --> 58:29.570
Where are we going?

58:29.572 --> 58:30.840
Right here.

58:34.976 --> 58:37.246
Careful. Okay?

58:41.250 --> 58:43.353
- Okay.
- Babe, it's a little cold.

58:44.253 --> 58:46.753
Stay, sit.

58:46.755 --> 58:48.858
Okay, in the dark?

58:49.791 --> 58:50.759
Ah.

58:52.460 --> 58:55.494
What's gotten into you?

58:55.496 --> 58:56.662
Remember when you said
there wasn't

58:56.664 --> 58:58.601
enough magic in the world?

58:59.434 --> 59:00.402
Yeah.

59:03.472 --> 59:06.873
Okay, this is not
what I had in mind.

59:06.875 --> 59:09.376
Promise me you won't get mad.

59:09.378 --> 59:11.979
Just hear me out.

59:11.981 --> 59:13.583
Something's happening, Hazel.

59:15.818 --> 59:17.754
Something I can't explain.

59:18.786 --> 59:21.220
The day at the beach.

59:21.222 --> 59:24.758
Something from that day
is still with me.

59:24.760 --> 59:27.159
I keep getting pulled back
to that one day

59:27.161 --> 59:29.097
and I don't know why.

59:31.065 --> 59:33.001
I know this sounds crazy..

59:34.402 --> 59:36.338
...but if you're with me..

